verses.text: \w To|strong="H1732"\w* \w the|strong="H1732"\w* end, \w a|strong="H1732"\w* \w psalm|strong="H4210"\w* \w of|strong="H1732"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*. \w The|strong="H1732"\w* canticle \w of|strong="H1732"\w* Jeremias \w and|strong="H1732"\w* Ezechiel \w to|strong="H1732"\w* \w the|strong="H1732"\w* people \w of|strong="H1732"\w* \w the|strong="H1732"\w* captivity, when they began \w to|strong="H1732"\w* go out.

\w A|strong="H8085"\w* Hymn, \w O|strong="H8085"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, becometh thee \w in|strong="H0430"\w* Sion: \w and|strong="H0430"\w* \w a|strong="H8085"\w* vow shall \w be|strong="H0430"\w* \w paid|strong="H8085"\w* \w to|strong="H8085"\w* thee \w in|strong="H0430"\w* Jerusalem.
O hear \w my|strong="H5641"\w* prayer: all flesh shall come to thee.

\w The|strong="H0834"\w* \w words|strong="H1697"\w* \w of|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H0834"\w* wicked \w have|strong="H0834"\w* prevailed \w over|strong="H1869"\w* \w us|strong="H0834"\w*: \w and|strong="H2719"\w* thou wilt pardon \w our|strong="H0834"\w* transgressions.

Blessed \w is|strong="H3808"\w* \w he|strong="H3808"\w* whom thou hast chosen \w and|strong="H8535"\w* taken \w to|strong="H3808"\w* thee: \w he|strong="H3808"\w* \w shall|strong="H3808"\w* dwell \w in|strong="H3808"\w* thy courts. We \w shall|strong="H3808"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* filled with \w the|strong="H3372"\w* good \w things|strong="H3808"\w* \w of|strong="H3808"\w* thy house; holy \w is|strong="H3808"\w* thy temple,

Wonderful \w in|strong="H1697"\w* justice. Hear \w us|strong="H7200"\w*, \w O|strong="H4310"\w* \w God|strong="H0559"\w* \w our|strong="H7200"\w* saviour, \w who|strong="H4310"\w* art \w the|strong="H0559"\w* hope \w of|strong="H1697"\w* \w all|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H0559"\w* ends \w of|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H0559"\w* earth, \w and|strong="H2388"\w* \w in|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H0559"\w* sea afar \w off|strong="H5608"\w*.
Thou \w who|strong="H0376"\w* preparest \w the|strong="H7130"\w* mountains \w by|strong="H0376"\w* thy strength, being girded \w with|strong="H0376"\w* power:

\w Who|strong="H0430"\w* troublest \w the|strong="H1961"\w* depth \w of|strong="H0430"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* sea, \w the|strong="H1961"\w* noise \w of|strong="H0430"\w* \w its|strong="H1961"\w* waves. \w The|strong="H1961"\w* Gentiles shall \w be|strong="H1961"\w* troubled,

\w And|strong="H7200"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* dwell \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* uttermost borders \w shall|strong="H3956"\w* \w be|strong="H3605"\w* afraid \w at|strong="H5921"\w* thy signs: thou shalt \w make|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* outgoings \w of|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* morning \w and|strong="H7200"\w* \w of|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* evening \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w be|strong="H3605"\w* joyful.

Thou hast visited \w the|strong="H3605"\w* earth, \w and|strong="H0430"\w* hast plentifully watered \w it|strong="H3605"\w*; thou hast many ways enriched \w it|strong="H3605"\w*. \w The|strong="H3605"\w* river \w of|strong="H0430"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w* \w is|strong="H0430"\w* filled \w with|strong="H0430"\w* water, thou hast prepared \w their|strong="H3605"\w* food: \w for|strong="H3605"\w* so \w is|strong="H0430"\w* \w its|strong="H3605"\w* preparation.

Fill \w up|strong="H3605"\w* plentifully \w the|strong="H3605"\w* streams thereof, multiply \w its|strong="H3605"\w* fruits; \w it|strong="H3068"\w* \w shall|strong="H3068"\w* spring \w up|strong="H3605"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w rejoice|strong="H8055"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w its|strong="H3605"\w* showers.
Thou shalt bless the crown of the year of thy goodness: and thy fields shall be filled with plenty.
The beautiful places of the wilderness shall grow fat: and the hills shall be girded about with joy,
The rams of the flock are clothed, and the vales shall abound with corn: they shall shout, yea they shall sing a hymn.
